  <h4 class="pHead4" >
</h4>    

<a name="wp3680300"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
Description
</h3>    

<a name="wp3680301"> </a><p class="pBody" >
The <code class="cCodeBody">assert_implication</code> assertion checker checks the single-bit expression <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">antecedent_expr</span> at each rising edge of <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">clk</span>.  If <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">antecedent_expr</span> is TRUE, then the checker verifies that the value of <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">consequent_expr</span> is also TRUE. If <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">antecedent_expr</span> is not TRUE, then the assertion is valid regardless of the value of <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">consequent_expr</span>.
</p>    
<a name="wp3680310"> </a><h4 class="pHead4" >
Assertion Check  </h4>    <div align="left" class="tbl">
<table border="0">
  <caption></caption>
  <tr align="left" valign="top">    <td><a name="wp3680305"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
&#160;
</div>    
</td>
    <td><a name="wp3680307"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
ASSERT_IMPLICATION
</div>    
</td>
    <td><a name="wp3680309"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
Expression evaluated to FALSE.
</div>    
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
	
  <h4 class="pHead4" >
</h4>    

