cover_antecedent
</div>    
</td>
    <td><a name="wp3681332"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
The <em class="cEmphasis">antecedent_expr</em>  evaluated to TRUE.
</div>    
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
	
  <h4 class="pHead4" >
</h4>    

<a name="wp3681246"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
Notes
</h3>    

<a name="wp3681247"> </a><p class="pNumber" >
 1.	This assertion checker is equivalent to:
</p>    
<p class="pCodeShiftTop"></p><a name="wp3681278"> </a><pre class="pCode3" >	assert_always 
</pre>    <a name="wp3771982"> </a><pre class="pCode3" >		[#(<em class="cEmphasis">severity_level</em>, <em class="cEmphasis">property_type</em>,<em class="cEmphasis"> msg</em>,<em class="cEmphasis"> coverage_level </em>)] 
</pre>    <a name="wp3771983"> </a><pre class="pCode3" >		<em class="cEmphasis">instance_name</em> (<em class="cEmphasis">clk, reset_n,  </em>(<em class="cEmphasis">antecedent_expr</em>  ? <em class="cEmphasis">consequent_expr </em> : 1&#8217;b1 ));
</pre>    
<p class="pCodeShiftBottom"></p>
<a name="wp3680313"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
See also
</h3>    

<p class="pCodeShiftTop"></p><a name="wp3680314"> </a><pre class="pCode2" >assert_always, assert_always_on_edge, assert_never, assert_proposition
</pre>    
